string.value: All passive skills are applied by default.
Other player's AoE skills will not be visible.
You can start by selecting the Start Party \noption, even with a small party.
The more players you play with, the higher the chances of getting better rewards.
If you force close during play, \nyou won't receive the reward.
The damage other players inflict \nwill show on Ursus's back.
If you enter certain maps while on the waitlist, \nyou might lose your place.
You can start in a 1-player-party, but it's easier with more players.
Ursus has a locational damage system, \nmeaning he takes different damage \nto different parts.
Damage effects are displayed in 3 stages.
Players that are bit and tossed by Ursus\n will be KO'd unless another player \ncatches them.
If you don't get on top of Ursus \nwhen he is down, you may be KO'd \nby his attack.
If a bomb appears on your head,\n get your allies to join you to \nspread the damage out.
Players who are hit by dirt can be saved\n if another player touches them.
Jump when Ursus stomps to limit \nthe damage taken.
Use the Tab key during the battle\n to check on your teammates.
The rewards will change depending on \nyour contribution.
The final score is the sum of the team \nand individual scores.
The more players you save, the better your rewards will be.
Ursus is the first monster in MapleStory \nthat uses the new skeletal animation system.
Ursus's name at birth was "Veronica".
Some chain attacks that come after\n being bitten by Ursus can cause \nmental breakdowns.
